  "2026-05-25T19:47:52.441Z",codex-full-audit,"Code-quality/security audit note 2026-05-25: tracked secret scan is clean and static quality passes. Sub-agent review still found pack/build hygiene and complexity follow-ups outside this safe slice: build does not clean stale dist artifacts before packing, several modules remain large/complex, and mutation output verbosity overlaps pm-ch59. No private telemetry host/token material was found in tracked files by scripts/check-secrets.mjs. Keep this item open for larger dist-clean/complexity work."
  "2026-05-25T20:08:30.926Z",codex-code-quality-specialist,"Code-quality specialist evidence 2026-05-25: repo size/complexity scan found no static-quality violations, but maintainability risk remains. Size snapshot: 141315 LOC across src/tests/docs/packages/plugins; largest files include tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts 6989 LOC, tests/unit/extension-loader.spec.ts 3339 LOC, src/cli/commands/update.ts 1936 LOC, src/core/extensions/loader.ts 1929 LOC, src/cli/main.ts 1895 LOC. jscpd scan (npx -y jscpd --min-lines 24 --min-tokens 120 --reporters json --output /tmp/pm-cli-jscpd src tests docs packages plugins) took 41.806s and found 5 clone clusters / 260 duplicated lines / 0.33%. Generated duplicates: plugin MCP wrappers and package runtime loaders. Hand-maintained duplicates to consider: src/core/extensions/extension-policy.ts:156-183 duplicated at 277-303, and src/cli/commands/history-redact.ts:532-558 duplicated with src/cli/commands/history-repair.ts:171-197. Recommended fix: keep generated duplicate allowlist explicit, extract shared override normalization and shared history rewrite lock/ownership helper, and lower static-quality thresholds once these known long files are split."
  "2026-05-25T20:23:56.238Z",ci-quality-subagent,"CI/test maintainability evidence 2026-05-25: latest scan confirms pm-3cbk should stay open. Long-file hotspots remain tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts 6989 LOC, tests/unit/extension-loader.spec.ts 3339 LOC, tests/unit/test-command.spec.ts 2029 LOC, src/cli/commands/update.ts 1936 LOC, src/core/extensions/loader.ts 1929 LOC, src/cli/main.ts 1895 LOC, and tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts 1894 LOC. static-quality-gate still passes under current thresholds (max_test_lines 7000, max_src_lines 3400, max_complexity 260), so there is no immediate gate violation, but the thresholds are permissive. Recommendation remains to split high-volume integration specs by workflow and migrate subprocess-heavy clusters to runCliInProcess with a small retained subprocess parity set; lower thresholds only after those known files are split."
  "2026-05-26T15:43:50.566Z",claude-code-agent,"Linking dedup extraction follow-up to branch fix/nightly-cross-platform-stability-and-extension-policy-dedup: extracting buildExtensionPolicyOverride helper within extension-policy.ts (single-file extraction, no coverage gate change because the file is already in the uncovered allowlist). Removes 25-line duplicate between normalizeExtensionPolicy/hydrateExtensionPolicy override loops."
  "2026-05-26T15:53:41.309Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation evidence 2026-05-26: extracted buildExtensionPolicyOverride + collectExtensionPolicyOverrides helpers inside src/core/extensions/extension-policy.ts (single-file, no coverage-include change needed because the file is already in the uncovered allowlist). Removed 25-line duplicate between normalizeExtensionPolicy and hydrateExtensionPolicy override loops. The decision pattern is preserved: the existing barrel re-export structure is untouched; consumers continue to import {normalize,hydrate}ExtensionPolicy with no changes. Verified via extension-loader/settings-store/settings-validator/contracts-command tests (90 tests pass) and full release gate (coverage stays at 100%, static-quality gate passes)."
  "2026-05-26T16:23:02.523Z",claude-code-agent,"Slice merged 2026-05-26 via PR #73 (commit 60659285): buildExtensionPolicyOverride + collectExtensionPolicyOverrides extraction inside extension-policy.ts removed the 25-line override-loop duplicate. pm-3cbk remains open as the umbrella decision for further barrel/dedup work (jscpd still flags pm.history-redact <-> history-repair lock+ownership pattern as a candidate; extracting that needs a new src/core/history/history-rewrite.ts plus an uncovered-allowlist entry, deferred to keep this slice tight)."
  "2026-05-26T22:03:10.187Z",codex-active-continuation,"Kickoff 2026-05-26 (codex-active-continuation): claimed maintainability support slice for the consolidated perf/reliability PR. This run will apply pm-3cbk decision guidance while expanding in-process test runner adoption and any startup/reliability dedup work, keeping explicit coverage governance and changelog-generation policy intact.\n\nGitHub/security kickoff snapshot for this item aligns with the umbrella comment on pm-rnpb (open issues/PRs 0, dependabot/secret alerts 0, code scanning unavailable in current token scope, pnpm audit clean)."
  "2026-05-26T22:29:38.175Z",codex-active-continuation,"Decision-aligned maintainability update:\n- Added explicit selective registration helper surface in src/cli/register-list-query.ts (commandFilter + shouldRegisterListQueryCommand) instead of copy/paste command wiring.\n- Kept alias-safe handling (context/ctx) centralized in helper logic.\n- Wired core selection in src/cli/main.ts with narrow command filter propagation while preserving full-family behavior for broad/help invocations.\n- Regression suite validates no behavior drift in list/search/get/help/release-readiness command contracts."
